## Part 2: Guided Implementation (90 minutes)

### Step 1: Create Solver Skeleton

**Action:** Create basic solver structure

```bash
cd src/myContinuitySolver
touch myContinuitySolver.C createFields.H
mkdir -p Make
touch Make/files Make/options
```

**File:** `Make/files`
```makefile
myContinuitySolver.C

EXE = $(FOAM_USER_APPBIN)/myContinuitySolver
```

**File:** `Make/options`
```makefile
EXE_INC = \
    -I$(LIB_SRC)/finiteVolume/lnInclude \
    -I$(LIB_SRC)/meshTools/lnInclude \
    -I$(LIB_SRC)/fvModels/lnInclude

EXE_LIBS = \
    -lfiniteVolume \
    -lfvModels \
    -lmeshTools
```

**C++ Concept:** File organization and preprocessor directives
- **Why:** `#include` brings in declarations, `EXE_INC` tells compiler where to find headers
- **CFD Connection:** OpenFOAM's finiteVolume library contains all FVM operators

---

### Step 2: Create Main Solver File

**File:** `myContinuitySolver.C`

```cpp
#include "fvCFD.H"
#include "fvModels.H"
#include "fvConstraints.H"

int main(int argc, char *argv[])
{
    #include "setRootCase.H"
    #include "createTime.H"
    #include "createMesh.H"
    #include "createFields.H"

    Info<< "\nStarting continuity equation solver\n" << endl;
    Info<< "Ground truth: openfoam_temp/src/finiteVolume/cfdTools/compressible/rhoEqn.H:32-46\n" << endl;

    // Track initial mass
    scalar initialMass = fvc::domainIntegrate(rho).value();
    Info<< "Initial mass in domain: " << initialMass << " kg" << nl << endl;

    while (runTime.loop())
    {
        Info<< "Time = " << runTime.timeName() << nl << endl;

        // --- Continuity equation
        // Reference: openfoam_temp/src/finiteVolume/cfdTools/compressible/rhoEqn.H
        // Formula: ∂ρ/∂t + ∇·(ρU) = S_ρ

        fvScalarMatrix rhoEqn
        (
            fvm::ddt(rho)      // ∂ρ/∂t : Implicit temporal derivative
          + fvc::div(phi)      // ∇·(ρU) : Explicit convective term (phi = ρU·Sf)
          ==
            fvModels.source(rho)  // S_ρ : Source terms from fvModels
        );

        fvConstraints.constrain(rhoEqn);
        rhoEqn.solve();
        fvConstraints.constrain(rho);

        // --- Continuity error calculation
        // Reference: openfoam_temp/src/finiteVolume/cfdTools/incompressible/continuityErrs.H
        volScalarField contErr
        (
            fvc::ddt(rho) + fvc::div(phi) - fvModels.source(rho)
        );

        scalar sumLocalContErr = runTime.deltaTValue() *
            mag(contErr)().weightedAverage(mesh.V()).value();
        scalar globalContErr = runTime.deltaTValue() *
            contErr.weightedAverage(mesh.V()).value();

        Info<< "Continuity error : sum local = " << sumLocalContErr
            << ", global = " << globalContErr << endl;

        // --- Mass conservation check
        scalar currentMass = fvc::domainIntegrate(rho).value();
        scalar massChange = currentMass - initialMass;

        Info<< "Mass conservation : initial = " << initialMass
            << ", current = " << currentMass
            << ", change = " << massChange << nl << endl;

        runTime.write();

        Info<< "ExecutionTime = " << runTime.elapsedCpuTime() << " s"
            << "  ClockTime = " << runTime.elapsedClockTime() << " s"
            << nl << endl;
    }

    Info<< "End\n" << endl;

    return 0;
}
```

**C++ Concept:** Templates (`tmp<fvMatrix<Type>>`)
- **What happens:** `fvm::ddt(rho)` returns `tmp<fvScalarMatrix>`, a smart pointer
- **Why:** Enables automatic memory management and type safety for different field types
- **CFD Connection:** Same code works for scalars, vectors, tensors

**Reference:** `openfoam_temp/src/finiteVolume/finiteVolume/fvm/fvmDdt.H:54-58`

